Package: freenic
Title: Access the freenic US Banking Regulatory Database
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Nick", "Andersen", , "andenick@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Read-only access to the freenic database of US banking
    regulatory data spanning 1863-2026. Provides functions to read
    34 Parquet-format tables covering 1.5 billion observations from
    20 data sources including FFIEC, FDIC, Federal Reserve, and more.
    Data is accessed via Apache Arrow Parquet readers.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    rlang
Suggests:
    arrow (>= 14.0),
    dplyr,
    DBI,
    duckdb,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
